<p>When I run the following program on ubuntu 10.04 and 14.04, I notice that 14.04 is 22% slower. Any ideas?</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; #include &lt;stdlib.h&gt; #include &lt;string.h&gt; #include &lt;time.h&gt; #include &lt;sys/time.h&gt;  int func() {    char* b = (char *) malloc(4096);    free(b);    return(0); }  int main(int argc, char** argv) {    int i;     struct timeval start, end;    gettimeofday(&amp;start, NULL);     for (i = 0; i &lt; atoi(argv[1]); i++)    {        func();    }    gettimeofday(&amp;end, NULL);    printf("time taken is %ld seconds\n", end.tv_sec - start.tv_sec); } </code></pre>  <p>The behavior is consistent. The hardware of the two machines is identical.</p>